The Department of Correctional Services (DCS), working with the South African Police Services (SAPS) are on a manhunt, this after four prisoners escaped from Kgosi Mampuru II correctional service today (Saturday). According to the Department spokeswoman, Zandile Mabunda, three of the escapees are Zimbabwe Nationals, while one was South African. She said they were arrested for various crimes such as theft, armed robbery and house breaking.She said an investigation has been conducted, and the circumstances relating to the escape will be known once the investigation has been concluded. She said their names are Morris Tyavana, Medicine Girenzi, Amos Chikwange and Sam Hlungwane. "The Department is appealing to the public to assist with any information that may lead to their re-arrest," she said. 